PRIOENC
Priority encoder.
Returns the index of the highest active bit in the input value.
PRIOENC() is a combinational function with no internal state.
There is no panel UI in v1 — logic only.

───

Syntax
text
Ybit index =
PRIOENC(Xbit value)

Where:
text
Xbit

is any bit width.
The return width is:
text
ceil(log2(X))

bits.

───

Behavior
The highest set bit has priority.
Example:
text
00101010

contains active bits:
text
bit 5
bit 3
bit 1

Result:
text
101

because bit 5 is the highest active bit.

───

Return width

Input width
Return width

2bit
1bit

4bit
2bit

8bit
3bit

16bit
4bit

32bit
5bit

