───

Comparison with MUX
A priority encoder can be constructed manually using nested MUX operations.
Example:
text
MUX(
  requests.7,
  111,

  MUX(
    requests.6,
    110,

    MUX(
      requests.5,
      101,
      ...
    )
  )
)

PRIOENC() is a compact built-in equivalent.

───

Common Errors

Error
Cause

PRIOENC expects exactly one argument
Wrong parameter count

PRIOENC argument must be a bit value
Invalid argument type

Cannot infer output width
Invalid assignment target width

Bit-width mismatch
Assigned wire width does not match return width



───

Notes
Priority is always assigned to the highest set bit.
Example:
text
00101010

returns:
text
101

(bit 5)
not:
text
001

(bit 1)
There is no low-priority variant in v1.
